Model the following Car Showroom information as a graph model,and answer
the queries using Cypher. Consider a car showroom with different models of
cars like sofas Honda city, Skoda, Creta, Swift, Ertiga etc. Showroom is
divided into different sections, onesection for each car model; each section is
handled by a sales staff. Asales staff can handle one or more sections.
Customer may enquire about car. An enquiry may result in a purchase by the
customer.

Identify the labels and relationships, along with their properties, and
draw a high-level Graph model.

Create nodes and relationships, along with their properties, and
visualize your actual Graph model.
CREATE (s1:SalesStaff {name:'Mr. Narayan', employee_id:101}),
(s2:SalesStaff {name:'Ms. Priya', employee_id:102});

CREATE (sec1:Section {name:'Section A'}),
(sec2:Section {name:'Section B'}),
(sec3:Section {name:'Section C'}),
(sec4:Section {name:'Section D'});

CREATE (c1:CarModel {name:'Honda City', price:1200000}),
(c2:CarModel {name:'Skoda', price:1500000}),
(c3:CarModel {name:'Creta', price:1300000}),
(c4:CarModel {name:'Swift', price:700000}),
(c5:CarModel {name:'Ertiga', price:900000});

CREATE
(s1)-[:HANDLES]->(sec1),
(s1)-[:HANDLES]->(sec2),
(s2)-[:HANDLES]->(sec3),
(s2)-[:HANDLES]->(sec4),

(sec1)-[:HAS]->(c1),
(sec2)-[:HAS]->(c2),
(sec3)-[:HAS]->(c3),
(sec4)-[:HAS]->(c4),
(sec4)-[:HAS]->(c5);

CREATE (cust1:Customer {name:'Ramesh', contact:'1234567890'}),
(cust2:Customer {name:'Sita', contact:'9876543210'}),
(cust3:Customer {name:'Rahul', contact:'5555555555'});

CREATE
(cust1)-[:ENQUIRED]->(c1),
(cust1)-[:PURCHASED]->(c1),
(cust2)-[:ENQUIRED]->(c2),
(cust3)-[:ENQUIRED]->(c3);

Answer the following queries:
a. List the types of cars available in the showroom.
MATCH (c:CarModel)
RETURN c.name AS CarModel;

b. List the sections handled by Mr. Narayan.

c. List the names of customers who have done only enquiry but not
made any purchase.
d. List the highly sale car model.